{"lemma":"جُونٌ","slug":"جُونٌ","root":"ج.#.ن","root_slug":"ج-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6770"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bay, inlet, gulf, lagoon"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name from English, equivalent to English John"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"reddish-black","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"وَشِمِلَّةٍ حَرْفٍ كَأَنَّ قُتُودَهَا … جَلَّلْتُهَا (var. لَبَسْتُهَا) جَوْنَ السَّرَاةِ خَفَيْدَدًا","english":"Some hardy she-camel the saddle-woods of which I applied like upon a black-backed ostrich"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Equivalent to English lagoon, via a Romance source with the la- part interpreted as article.\n\nFrom English John.\n\nFrom Middle Persian [script needed] (gwn' /⁠gōn⁠/, “colour, complexion”), equalling Classical Persian گون (gūn)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6770","headword_ar":"جَوْنٌ","root":"jwn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) thus bearing two contr. significations: (S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwniY~N","text_ar":"جُونِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, has the latter signification: (IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwt","text_ar":"حوت"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawonN","text_ar":"جَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black tinged over with red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black intermixed with red;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"colour of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaA","text_ar":"قَطَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a pure red colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, applied to a horse and a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoham","text_ar":"اَدْهَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) every camel, and every wild ass, seen from a distance, is of this colour: fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) and, applied to a plant, or herbage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining to blackness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwnN","text_ar":"جُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SutomN","text_ar":"صُتْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SatomN","text_ar":"صَتْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wurodN","text_ar":"وُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warodN","text_ar":"وَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu jawonapN","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ جَوْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun is characterized by what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwnapN","text_ar":"جُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is intensely glistening and clear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawonapN","text_ar":"جَوْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwniY~N","text_ar":"جُونِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Accord. to ISk,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Aljawoni","text_ar":"اَبُو الجَوْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The white man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuwAlbayoDaA='i","text_ar":"اَبُوالبَيْضَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the negro. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byD","text_ar":"بيض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, K:) pl. as above. (K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"gay~ara yaA binota AlHulayosi lawoniY\n                      \n                     \n                        mar~u All~ayaAliY waA@xotilaAfu Aljuwoni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The passing of the nights, and the alternating of the day, have changed, O daughter of El-Holeys, my colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AO, S.) ―         -b3-  And, accord. to certain of the lawyers, metaphorically, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-  And accord. to IAar, (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frq","text_ar":"فرق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraq","text_ar":"فَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day-break"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljawonaAni","text_ar":"الجَوْنَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two extremities of the bow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Az, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","T","M","TA","AO"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}